sanctions resolution when it comes before the Security Council. 
</P>
<P>
 * In response to the vote in Vienna, Pyongyang quickly renounced its 
obligations to cooperate with inspectors and expelled two international 
observers. This action, analysts suggested, could heighten support in the 
United Nations for a sanctions resolution. 
</P>
