WEST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: PORT HUENEME; GIRL, 13, INJURED IN HIT-AND-RUN CRASH 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MARY F. POLS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 13-year-old Port Hueneme girl who was struck by a hit-and-run driver was 
hospitalized in good condition Friday night, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 The girl, Missey States, was crossing Ventura Road in the crosswalk when she 
was struck by a car that was turning off Bard Road, said investigating officer 
Ron Burns.She was with a friend, who was not injured in the 2:20 p.m. incident. 
</P>
<P>
 "She was terrified," Burns said. "She was dragged 40 feet by the car." 
</P>
<P>
 The driver of the car, identified by Port Hueneme police as Larry Fisher, 49, 
of Oxnard, was arrested a block from the scene on suspicion of driving under 
the influence and felony hit and run. 
</P>
<P>
 A spokeswoman for St. John's Regional Medical Center said the girl suffered 
multiple scrapes. 
</P>
<P>
 Burns said Fisher reportedly got out of the car and looked at the girl after 
she was struck. A security officer at the Port Hueneme naval base witnessed the 
accident and responded almost immediately. Burns said Fisher then got in his 
car and began to drive away.MARY F. POLS 
</P>
