<HEADLINE>
<P>
EAST VENTURA COUNTY FOCUS: THOUSAND OAKS; SCHOOL BOARD OKS 5% HIKE IN BUS FARE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Riding the bus to school in Thousand Oaks will be a little more expensive this 
fall. 
</P>
<P>
 The Conejo Valley school board on Thursday unanimously approved a 5% increase 
in school bus fares.A semester's worth of round-trip rides will now cost $190, 
up from $180 this school year. One-way rides for a semester will cost $100, up 
from $95. 
</P>
<P>
 School officials said the fare hike was necessary to cover inflation. The 
Conejo Valley Unified School District began charging parents for bus service in 
1992 as a way of recouping $600,000 spent on transportation from the district's 
general fund. Even with the higher fees, the district still expects to 
subsidize bus service by about $20,000 next year. 
</P>
<P>
 Special-education students do not pay for bus service, nor do students who 
qualify for free or reduced-fare rides. About 6% of the district's 17,000 
students rely on school bus service, officials said. JULIE FIELDS 
</P>
</TEXT>
