 Let's get this straight. Nobody owes Pat Riley or the Knicks a damn thing. 
Several seasons of being ousted in the playoffs when they supposedly should 
have moved on means nothing. Especially to those outside of New York. With two 
games practically given to the Knicks on questionable calls (in New York), how 
can Riley already be speaking in terms of "fate" and "destiny." Nobody owes you 
anything, Riley, and you'll find that out on the road in Houston. 
</P>
