 BILL HAZELTON 
</P>
<P>
 Santa Barbara 
</P>
<P>
 * 
</P>
<P>
 So Allan Malamud thinks this year's NBA playoffs have been "the dullest in 
recent memory"? 
</P>
<P>
 Let's recap some of the incredibly boring events that we have had to endure so 
far: The top-seeded team in the West is upset by the eighth seed. There have 
been record-tying comebacks (Houston over Phoenix); record-setting comebacks 
(Denver over Seattle); exemplary offensive performances (Barkley's 56, 
Olajuwon's 46 and Miller's fourth-quarter heroics); fights, bench-clearing 
brawls, fines and suspensions; a changing of the guard as the Bulls bow out, 
and, oh yes, some highly competitive basketball with a number of series being 
stretched to the limit. 
</P>
<P>
 If these playoffs are dull, I can't wait until they get interesting again. 
</P>
<P>
 RUSTY THOMAS 
</P>
<P>
 Los Angeles 
