<HEADLINE>
<P>
A BENEFIT IN THE BALLROOM 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By ZAN DUBIN, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Some of the country's top competitive ballroom dancers -- including a few from 
Orange County -- will whirl, dip and shimmy here Sunday to raise money for 
Western Medical Center-Bartlett, a nonprofit long-term rehabilitation facility 
in Santa Ana. 
</P>
<P>
 The second annual Ballroom Dance Extravaganza will be from 4 to 9 p.m. at the 
Newport Beach Marriott Hotel and Tennis Club, 900 Newport Center Drive.It 
offers a chance to watch such leading couples as Victor Veyrasset and Heather 
Smith and Michael and Jacqueline Kuka of Los Angeles, and Melissa Dexter and 
Geir Baake of San Diego. 
</P>
<P>
 County residents out on the floor will include Peter Siddall and Marylynn 
Benitez of Irvine, Stuart Cole and Maria Hansen of Costa Mesa, and youth 
competitor Heidi Groskreutz, also of Costa Mesa, who will share the limelight 
with Benji Schwimmer of Riverside County. 
</P>
<P>
 Tickets -- $35, $50 and $100, with all proceeds benefiting the medical center 
-- include a kickoff buffet at which attendees will be able to meet the gowned 
and tuxedoed performers. The dancing -- ballroom, Latin and jazz, in couples 
and in groups -- will start at 6; a 30-minute intermission will give those in 
the audience their own opportunity to cut the rug. 
</P>
<P>
 Attire: "dressy casual." Information: (714) 973-1656. 
</P>
</TEXT>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061194-0103 </DOCNO>
<DOCID> 050360 </DOCID>
<SOURCE>
<P>
 Los Angeles Times 
</P>
</SOURCE>
<DATE>
<P>
June 11, 1994, Saturday, Home Edition 
</P>
