<HEADLINE>
<P>
A LOSS TO THE DISTRICT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Santa Ana Unified School District needs a breath of fresh air but it won't 
happen when (Superintendent) Rudy Castruita leaves the district ("Castruita 
Will Quit Santa Ana School District," June 1). The breath of fresh air will 
come when the conservative Christian groups who oppose school reform are voted 
out of office. 
</P>
<P>
 Talk about no class, (board member) Tom Chaffee makes a remark in regards to 
Castruita leaving by saying we "need a breath of fresh air and I can't say I'm 
sorry to see him go." Nice going, Tom. Why not just wish him well and let it go 
at that? 
</P>
<P>
 Watch out folks! Pay attention because these Christian conservative groups are 
infiltrating many school districts with unrealistic ideas and no idea of what 
is really going on in schools today. During Castruita's reign, there have been 
two National Blue Ribbon Schools and 10 California Distinguished School awards. 
Three schools were honored last month but some board members seem to find fault 
with everything Dr. Castruita and a hard-working staff have accomplished. 
</P>
<P>
 Wonderful things are happening in schools today but people like (Rosemarie) 
Avila and Chaffee do not build but tear down and in turn lose will, lose 
superior administrators and teachers because of their ignorance -- or is this 
their plan?  
</P>
<P>
 ELEANOR A. ROTHAERMEL 
</P>
<P>
 Laguna Hills 
</P>
</TEXT>
