<HEADLINE>
<P>
METROPOLITAN DIGEST / LOS ANGELES COUNTY NEWS IN BRIEF: ANTELOPE VALLEY; CLAS 
TEST OFFERED UNDER COURT ORDER; FEW TAKE IT 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 The Antelope Valley Union High School district offered the controversial 
California Learning Assessment System tests Friday under court order, but only 
460 of 3,000 sophomores chose to take it. 
</P>
<P>
 Most students decided not to take it because it conflicted with preparations 
for final exams. 
</P>
<P>
 Students who took the CLAS test said they were motivated by a variety of 
reasons, with many saying they were unhappy that the district's Board of 
Education prevented them from taking it earlier. 
</P>
<P>
 The board had voted 3 to 2 to boycott the tests, citing objections to the 
content and style of the statewide exams. 
