<HEADLINE>
<P>
WEST VALLEY FOCUS: WESTLAKE VILLAGE; CATCH-BASIN CLEANING TO LIMIT ODORS, PESTS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 San Fernando Valley residents can look forward to better drainage, fewer 
rodents and a decrease in foul odors, once this year's catch basin clean-out 
kicks off in August. 
</P>
<P>
 The clean-out effort by the Los Angeles County Department of Public Works is 
scheduled to take nine weeks. It will involve about 5,400 catch basins -- the 
gutters between the curb and the street -- in the area between the beaches to 
just west of downtown, Westlake Village and the incorporated zones around it. 
</P>
<P>
 Drainage cleaning is conducted annually and expected to cost between $40,000 
and $50,000. MAKI BECKER 
</P>
</TEXT>
<TYPE>
<P>
Column; Brief 
</P>
</TYPE>
</DOC>
<DOC>
<DOCNO> LA061194-0164 </DOCNO>
