<HEADLINE>
<P>
IN A FIERY RELATIONSHIP, RISON'S GIRLFRIEND SURRENDERS 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
From Associated Press 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Hip-hop performer Lisa (Left Eye) Lopes surrendered to police Friday on 
charges that she set fire to the two-story mansion belonging to her boyfriend, 
Atlanta Falcon receiver Andre Rison, and smashed his cars. 
</P>
<P>
 Lopes, 22, a singer with the group TLC, is accused of felony arson and 
criminal damage to property.The house was destroyed in the Thursday blaze. 
</P>
<P>
 Court officials said Lopes waived her right to a hearing in Fulton County 
magistrate's court that had been scheduled for Monday. It was unclear when the 
singer, whose nickname comes from her habit of replacing one lens of her 
glasses with a condom during performances, would appear in court. 
</P>
<P>
 Magistrate Vickie Moran set bond at $500,000 on the arson charge and $10,000 
on a criminal damage charge. Lopes also is accused of smashing Rison's cars. 
The bond was later reduced to $82,000, which Lopes posted. 
</P>
<P>
 Police also said they would charge Lopes with a misdemeanor drug charge 
because of marijuana found in the burned-out home. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said an enraged Lopes set fire to cardboard in a whirlpool tub at the 
mansion around 6:30 a.m. Thursday after Rison and a group of friends returned 
from being out all night. 
</P>
<P>
 Rison said Lopes had been hitting him on the head that morning and he slapped 
her to get her to stop. 
</P>
<P>
 "That's when I went for a walk, before it went any further," he told WAGA-TV. 
"She's a beautiful person. . . . But I think there's something wrong with her 
mental state. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm in her corner. I'm going to go to bat for her." 
</P>
<P>
 Rison has had previous troubles with Lopes. Last September, he was arrested in 
a grocery parking lot after allegedly hitting Lopes and firing a handgun. The 
charges were later dismissed. 
</P>
</TEXT>
