<P>
NEWSWIRE: USC TO COMBINE MEN'S, WOMEN'S TRACK 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JIM HODGES, From Staff and Wire Reports 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 After a postseason review of the program, USC is combining its men's and 
women's track and field teams and seeking a coach who will be in charge of 
both. 
</P>
<P>
 Ron Allice, coach at Long Beach City College for 16 years, is a leading 
candidate for the Trojan job, and he said Friday he would be interested. 
</P>
<P>
 "It's a difficult situation, because I have a good job here know both of the 
coaches at USC and they have done a good job," Allice said. "And I've never 
spoken to Mike Garrett (Trojan athletic director)." 
</P>
<P>
 Men's Coach Jim Bush and women's Coach Barbara Edmondson were told this week 
about the switch after a review by Daryl Gross, USC assistant athletic 
director. Both coaches have been told that they will be invited back next 
season as part of the track and field staff. JIM HODGES 
</P>
</TEXT>
