<HEADLINE>
<P>
LOCAL NOTES: LONG BEACH STATE NAMES SHUMARD ASSISTANT ATHLETIC DIRECTOR 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By LON EUBANKS 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Bill Shumard, who resigned as athletic director at Cal State Fullerton 
effective at the end of May, has bounced back quickly. 
</P>
<P>
 Long Beach State announced Friday that Shumard will be the school's assistant 
athletic director for development and administration beginning on Monday. 
</P>
<P>
 Shumard, 43, is a 1972 graduate of Long Beach State. Shumard resigned after a 
troubled three-year tenure at Fullerton marked by unrest among 
student-athletes, the termination of the football program and a losing court 
battle in a wrongful termination suit brought by fired volleyball coach Jim 
Huffman. 
</P>
<P>
 "I'm excited, and I think it's going to be a real good fit for me," Shumard 
said. "It will get me back doing some things I really enjoy. I didn't want to 
move, and I'll be working for and with good people again." 
</P>
<P>
 Shumard will oversee the marketing, promotions and ticket operations in 
addition to assisting the athletic director with the daily operation of the 
department, said Dave O'Brien, Long Beach State athletic director. LON EUBANKS 
</P>
</TEXT>
