<HEADLINE>
<P>
CROOK, WATKINS LEAD EAST IN VENTURA COUNTY GAME 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By IRENE GARCIA, TIMES STAFF WRITER 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 With two of the East team's top players having bowed out of tonight's Ventura 
County high school all-star football game at Moorpark High, Marmonte League 
quarterbacks Kevin Crook and Jeremie Watkins will take center stage. 
</P>
<P>
 Newbury Park quarterback Keith Smith will not play in the game because he was 
drafted by the Detroit Tigers last week in the fifth round of baseball's 
amateur draft and does not want to risk injury. 
</P>
<P>
 Teammate Leodes Van Buren, a wide receiver, will not play because he is 
awaiting trial on a weapons charge. The 18-year-old has been charged with 
firing a gunshot into his girlfriend's Newbury Park home April 8. 
</P>
<P>
 Crook completed 173 passes for 2,736 yards and 21 touchdowns last season for 
Westlake. Simi Valley's Watkins completed 118 passes for 1,669 yards and 14 
touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 The West, coached by Buena's Rick Scott, will feature George Keiaho, a 
four-year starter at Buena and one of the state's top running backs. 
</P>
<P>
 Keiaho (5-foot-9, 215 pounds), who will play at Washington, rushed for 2,145 
yards and 28 touchdowns in 290 carries last season. 
</P>
<P>
 Rio Mesa's Donald DiDomizio and Santa Barbara's Brad Brunett are the West 
quarterbacks. DiDomizio, who was injured much of the season, rushed for 472 
yards and eight touchdowns. 
</P>
<P>
 "Their team is very large and we're strong at the skill positions," said 
Newbury Park's George Hurley, the East team's coach. "I think our team is also 
quicker and better at passing." 
</P>
<P>
 Kickoff is at 7 p.m. Tickets are $6 for adults and $4 for children. 
</P>
</TEXT>
