<P>
ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: SANTA ANA; CHILDREN TO GET FREE DENTAL CARE TODAY 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JON NALICK 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 About 200 children will receive free dental care today at Roosevelt Elementary 
School as part of Healthy Tomorrows, a school district program that offers 
preventive health care. 
</P>
<P>
 Four volunteer dentists will fill cavities and clean teeth, as well as refer 
children who need additional treatment for free follow-up visits.The value of 
the donated services is estimated at about $20,000, said Diane Thomas, 
spokeswoman for the Santa Ana Unified School District. 
</P>
<P>
 Children scheduled to receive treatment include those from Martin R. Heninger, 
John F. Kennedy and Roosevelt elementary schools. The service will be provided 
from 7:30 a.m. to noon at the Roosevelt campus, 501 S. Halladay St. 
</P>
<P>
 Bilingual parent education sessions will also be provided, and all health care 
services provided by Healthy Tomorrows are contingent on parental consent. 
</P>
<P>
 Healthy Tomorrows is operated at no cost to the district, Thomas said. JON 
NALICK 
</P>
</TEXT>
