ORANGE COUNTY FOCUS: COUNTYWIDE; COSTA MESAN NAMED TO OPTOMETRY BOARD 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<BYLINE>
<P>
By JAIME ABDO 
</P>
</BYLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Gov. Pete Wilson appointed a Costa Mesa man Friday to the state Board of 
Optometry. 
</P>
<P>
 Steven Grant is a 49-year-old optometrist who has been practicing since 1971. 
</P>
<P>
 The state Board of Optometry regulates more than 7,200 licensed optometrists 
and 400 optometric corporations in California. Its members are not paid and do 
not require state Senate confirmation. 
</P>
<P>
 Grant earned his bachelor of science and doctorate degrees from the Los 
Angeles College of Optometry.  
</P>
<P>
 He is the incoming president of the Costa Mesa North Kiwanis, and has served 
as a clinical instructor at the Southern California College of Optometry, 
president of the Orange County chapter of the American Academy of Optometry and 
president of the Turtle Rock Crest Homeowners Assn. JAIME ABDO 
</P>
