<P>
BICYCLIST DIES AFTER BEING STRUCK BY MINIVAN 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 A 57-year-old bicyclist died Friday of head wounds after he apparently ran a 
red light and was hit by a minivan, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Vinh Van Luu of Santa Ana was eastbound on Willits Street about 5:30 a.m. when 
he was struck by the minivan northbound on Fairview Street, Sgt. Dick Faust 
said. 
</P>
<P>
 "The minivan had the green light," Faust said. "The bicyclist had just been 
nearly hit by another car in that same intersection when the van came along." 
</P>
<P>
 Luu was thrown nearly 50 feet, from one side of the street to the other, and 
landed in the gutter, police said. He was not wearing a helmet. The unconscious 
man was taken to UCI Medical Center in Orange. He died nearly seven hours 
later, Faust said. 
</P>
<P>
 No one was cited in the accident, which is still under investigation, police 
said. 
</P>
