<HEADLINE>
<P>
ROBBERY THWARTED AT LIQUOR STORE 
</P>
</HEADLINE>
<TEXT>
<P>
 Two plainclothes police officers cut short an armed robbery by suspected gang 
members at a liquor store early Friday, authorities said. 
</P>
<P>
 While on a break at 1 a.m., officers Frank Gordon and Evan Sailor entered the 
Bal-Harbor liquor store in the 500 block of East Balboa Boulevard.Inside the 
store, police said, Gordon noticed a teen-ager standing near the cash register 
take a pistol out of his waistband. 
</P>
<P>
 However, when a second teen-ager -- apparently acting as a lookout just inside 
the front door -- signaled the arrival of another customer, the young man near 
the cash register returned his gun to his waistband, Gordon said. 
</P>
<P>
 Gordon signaled Sailer what was going on, and the two officers then drew their 
own weapons and stepped behind the suspected robbers and two suspected 
accomplices, ordering them to surrender, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Three of the youths complied, but the lookout fled to a nearby parking lot 
where he was captured by other officers alerted by the officers inside the 
store. 
</P>
<P>
 Those arrested were identified as members of a San Bernardino street gang. 
They included: Agustin Mesa and Manuel Leyva, both 18 and from San Bernardino; 
a 16-year-old boy from Rialto and a 14-year-old girl from Colton. 
</P>
<P>
 Each of the adults was being held in lieu of posting $50,000 bail at the 
Newport Beach Police Department jail facility, and the two juveniles were 
released to their parents, police said. 
</P>
<P>
 Police said that in addition to a pistol recovered from Mesa, officers found a 
second pistol in the group's car. 
</P>
